<div id="review_2720574627" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2720574627" />
    <a title="Dmitri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/73216705-dmitri"><img alt="Dmitri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1560026165p2/73216705.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2720574627?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dmitri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dmitri" href="/user/show/73216705-dmitri">Dmitri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73216705-dmitri?shelf=russia">russia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73216705-dmitri?shelf=europe">europe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2720574627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7417122581064642045">Once in a great while a history comes along that eclipses all others in the foreseeable future. And no, I am not Orlando Figes. This book has the passion and the pathos, the humor and the humanity. I guess that this is what they call literature. My only critique is the sheer weight of the volume and its mind numbingly tiny text. Couldn&apos;t this be reissued as an e-book?</span>
  <span id="freeText7417122581064642045" style="display:none">Once in a great while a history comes along that eclipses all others in the foreseeable future. And no, I am not Orlando Figes. This book has the passion and the pathos, the humor and the humanity. I guess that this is what they call literature. My only critique is the sheer weight of the volume and its mind numbingly tiny text. Couldn't this be reissued as an e-book?</span>
  <a data-text-id="7417122581064642045" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

